  <td class="diff-context"><div>Kravitz passed the business on to his sons Irving, Sollie and Al, who would often be seen working at the deli.&lt;ref name="cbc.ca"/&gt; At the height of its popularity, from the 1950s to the early 1980s, the restaurant had 75 employees. Customers often formed lunchtime line-ups that stretched around the block.&lt;ref name="therecord.com"&gt;http://www.therecord.com/whatson-story/4585711-new-exhibit-celebrates-montreal-deli/&lt;/ref&gt;</div></td>
